al culture, its place in Japanese cuisine, and the mercantile traditions that have shaped the marketplace since the early seventeenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMarketsxHistoryxJapanxTokyo. 0aMarketszJapanzTokyoxHistory. 0aSeafood industryxHistoryxJapanxTokyo. 0aSeafood industryzJapanzTokyoxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  a17th century.  aasian culture.  aasian history.  acase study.  aeast asia.  aeconomics.  aeconomy.  aethnography.  afieldwork.  afishmonger.  afoodways.  aglobalization.  ainternational.  ajapan.  ajapanese culture.  ajapanese food.  amarketplace.  apublic health.  aseafood trade.  aseafood.  asushi chef.  asushi.  atechnology.  atokyo.  atourism.  atourist trap.  atourist.  atsukiji.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092358440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520923584423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520923584/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles